Can you rewind a little bit?

83
00:04:31.855 --> 00:04:33.458
Some video store humor for you there.

84
00:04:33.482 --> 00:04:35.919
But. also. I mean it. Go back a little.

85
00:04:35.943 --> 00:04:38.046
Sure. Principal Anderson either

86
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:41.174
forgot to purchase the stop sign
he ordered for the school entrance.

87
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:44.386
or he got the school board to cough up
the money and took it for himself.

88
00:04:44.410 --> 00:04:47.555
Just like he did with the yield sign and
the two "no parking" signs by the track.

89
00:04:47.579 --> 00:04:49.599
Anderson requested and received

90
00:04:49.623 --> 00:04:53.228
$15.600 from the school board
for campus signs alone.

91
00:04:53.252 --> 00:04:55.480
And that doesn't even include
mousepads. tater tots.

92
00:04:55.504 --> 00:04:57.273
gym mats and a bunch of other stuff

93
00:04:57.297 --> 00:04:59.359
we found in the school budget
that doesn't exist in real life.

94
00:04:59.383 --> 00:05:00.568
Mm.

95
00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:02.070
Did you pay for that candy?

96
00:05:02.094 --> 00:05:05.907
As if I'm gonna put Blockbuster
out of business. They'll be fine.

97
00:05:05.931 --> 00:05:08.410
This is what got you fired
in the first place.

98
00:05:08.434 --> 00:05:10.495
All right. I know you're all
very excited by this theory.

99
00:05:10.519 --> 00:05:13.897
but I think you should direct
your amateur detective efforts elsewhere.

100
00:05:17.192 --> 00:05:18.920
What is he doing here?

101
00:05:18.944 --> 00:05:21.464
Hey. uh. Dustin called me. filled me in.

102
00:05:21.488 --> 00:05:23.800
Why would you do that?

103
00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:26.720
We can use the extra brainpower.

104
00:05:26.744 --> 00:05:28.263
Plus. he's Shannon's boyfriend.

105
00:05:28.287 --> 00:05:29.872
-Ex.
-Ex.

106
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:33.393
What am I missing?

107
00:05:33.417 --> 00:05:35.937
They're on
a friendship sabbatical.

108
00:05:35.961 --> 00:05:37.755
I'm just here to help.

109
00:05:41.216 --> 00:05:44.863
Anyway. you were Principal Anderson's
secretary for two years.

110
00:05:44.887 --> 00:05:47.115
Do you think
he could've stolen all that money?

111
00:05:47.139 --> 00:05:49.325
I don't know. He's such a rule follower.

112
00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:51.119
Well.

113
00:05:51.143 --> 00:05:54.289
the teachers love him. parents love him.

114
00:05:54.313 --> 00:05:57.292
He was just a finalist
for State Principal of the Year.

115
00:05:57.316 --> 00:05:58.376
The people spoke.

116
00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:01.212
But... but he sucks.

117
00:06:01.236 --> 00:06:05.717
Fine. but you can't just order things
and not buy them.

118
00:06:05.741 --> 00:06:08.344
There is a record.
And. plus. I would know.

119
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:11.556
I've spent hours
filing receipts and invoices.

120
00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:13.099
Did he have receipts
for the stuff we don't have?

121
00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:15.101
Mousepads? Tater tots? Gym mats?

122
00:06:15.125 --> 00:06:17.854
I don't know...
'cause I'm staying out of it.

123
00:06:17.878 --> 00:06:20.356
Hypothetically.
where would these receipts be?

124
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.818
In his file cabinet in his office.
which is always locked.

125
00:06:23.842 --> 00:06:26.029
-Can we break in?
-If it opens.

126
00:06:26.053 --> 00:06:27.822
-it can be broken into.
-How?

127
00:06:27.846 --> 00:06:32.893
I have a lot of bobby pins
from my French-twist period.

128
00:06:33.977 --> 00:06:35.705
-We steal Frank's master key.
-Got it.

129
00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:37.999
Wait. Frank the maintenance guy?
I thought he was fired.

130
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:41.002
His schedule got shifted to weekends.
Budget cuts.

131
00:06:41.026 --> 00:06:44.214
Yeah. good luck. When I'd ask
Frank for the key to the snack closet.

132
00:06:44.238 --> 00:06:46.091
-he'd say. "From my cold. dead hands."
-Right.

133
00:06:46.115 --> 00:06:48.718
because you have to pay for snacks.

134
00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:50.428
-They're... Okay.
-Okay. so let's say

135
00:06:50.452 --> 00:06:53.640
we somehow get into the school
on Saturday. get the key off Frank.

136
00:06:53.664 --> 00:06:55.725
-What do we do?
-We break into Anderson's office.

137
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:59.604
make copies of the receipts.
cross-reference them with the budget.

138
00:06:59.628 --> 00:07:02.023
If anything's missing. that's evidence
we can take to the school board.

139
00:07:02.047 --> 00:07:05.801
Easy. Now we just need an excuse
to be in school over the weekend.

140
00:07:08.846 --> 00:07:10.514
Guys?

141
00:07:20.357 --> 00:07:21.793
Hello. Rainier West High.

142
00:07:21.817 --> 00:07:24.879
This is Liz Miller coming to you live
from the AV room.

143
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:26.613
Please rise for the national anthem.

144
00:07:33.871 --> 00:07:35.223
♪ That girl thinks ♪

145
00:07:35.247 --> 00:07:37.433
♪ she's the queen of the neighborhood ♪

146
00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:40.645
-Coming through.
-♪ She's got the hottest trike in town ♪

147
00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:41.896
♪ That girl...

148
00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:43.731
Dustin. principal's office. now.

149
00:07:43.755 --> 00:07:45.108
♪ So high ♪

150
00:07:45.132 --> 00:07:46.442
♪ I think I wanna be...

151
00:07:46.466 --> 00:07:50.321
This period was not designed
