From the League of Women Voters.

159
00:08:20.876 --> 00:08:22.127
Huh.

160
00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:24.630
Thank you.

161
00:08:25.839 --> 00:08:26.965
Thank you.

162
00:08:28.967 --> 00:08:30.802
Head to the nurse's office.

163
00:08:34.932 --> 00:08:37.118
Listen up.

164
00:08:37.142 --> 00:08:40.205
"Operation: Manifest Anderson's Demise

165
00:08:40.229 --> 00:08:45.293
"by Breaking into His Office
to Expose His Hypocrisy" starts now.

166
00:08:45.317 --> 00:08:46.502
Subtle.

167
00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:48.504
Once the detention monitor
gets here.

168
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:52.008
we'll initiate Phase One:
key loop sabotage.

169
00:08:52.032 --> 00:08:55.136
I took the liberty
of fleshing out the plan a bit.

170
00:08:55.160 --> 00:08:56.411
What's that smell?

171
00:08:59.831 --> 00:09:02.477
Is this... lavender scented?

172
00:09:02.501 --> 00:09:04.938
Great nose. Liz.

173
00:09:04.962 --> 00:09:09.549
Lavender is a naturally calming fragrance.
and heists are known to be quite nervy.

174
00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:14.155
Whoa. When did detention get so uncool?

175
00:09:14.179 --> 00:09:15.698
I'm sorry. what are you doing here?

176
00:09:15.722 --> 00:09:19.726
Oh. turns out
nine tardies is six too many. so...

177
00:09:20.394 --> 00:09:24.123
Didn't expect to see
Good Girl Barbie serving time.

178
00:09:24.147 --> 00:09:27.818
What'd you do? Turn in an English essay
in the dialect of a Valley girl?

179
00:09:28.402 --> 00:09:30.421
I don't speak Valley.

180
00:09:30.445 --> 00:09:33.091
I only go there for sushi
and designer discounts.

181
00:09:33.115 --> 00:09:35.176
-Oh.
-Yeah. Elle's actually

182
00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:37.804
-the biggest badass here.
-Really?

183
00:09:37.828 --> 00:09:39.079
Enlighten me.

184
00:09:40.497 --> 00:09:43.768
Pie to Anderson in the face.
Don't want to talk about it.

185
00:09:43.792 --> 00:09:45.853
Elle Woods pied the principal.

186
00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:48.714
That's... shockingly epic.

187
00:09:49.464 --> 00:09:50.525
Thank you.

188
00:09:50.549 --> 00:09:54.404
But it's now 9:23 a.m.

189
00:09:54.428 --> 00:09:56.322
Does detention not start at 9:15?

190
00:09:56.346 --> 00:09:58.866
Where's our monitor?

191
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.183
Oh. here we go.

192
00:10:01.184 --> 00:10:02.436
I heard that.

193
00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:06.231
-You forgot your lunch.
-Oh. I didn't...

194
00:10:09.026 --> 00:10:12.547
I think someone might miss
being at school.

195
00:10:12.571 --> 00:10:16.676
Okay. delinquents.
here's how this is gonna work.

196
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:20.722
Every one of these books is
gonna be reshelved by 3:00 p.m..

197
00:10:20.746 --> 00:10:24.249
so get friendly
with our Dewey decimal system.

198
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:34.676
Phase One.

199
00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:52.444
May I please request the hall pass?

200
00:11:07.292 --> 00:11:08.919
Frank.

201
00:11:47.791 --> 00:11:49.543
Elle should be back by now.

202
00:11:51.503 --> 00:11:53.231
"9:15. cut key loop.

203
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:54.899
10:15. flood toilets."

204
00:11:54.923 --> 00:11:57.693
What is this
and why does it smell like my grandma?

205
00:11:57.717 --> 00:11:59.219
Not for you.

206
00:12:02.722 --> 00:12:06.786
Okay. you guys are being even more...
yourselves than usual.

207
00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:09.914
Did you Trojan horse yourselves
into detention? What's going on?

208
00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:11.124
Okay. why don't you go stack some books.

209
00:12:11.148 --> 00:12:13.709
I should know if I'm about to become
an unwitting accomplice

210
00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:15.527
to some lame secret operation.

211
00:12:16.570 --> 00:12:20.299
Guys. uh. she could actually be useful.

212
00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:21.509
-Oh. Thank you.
-Oh. why?

213
00:12:21.533 --> 00:12:23.386
Do we have a role
for an overly confident mean girl?

214
00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:26.514
Mrs. Martindale. I think my fellow
delinquents are up to something shady.

215
00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:28.266
Okay. you have no idea what you're doing.

216
00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:31.793
As I said moments ago.
I would love to be in the loop.

217
00:12:35.172 --> 00:12:38.901
Fine. We think someone here.
at a very high level.

218
00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:41.761
is embezzling money from the school.

219
00:12:43.430 --> 00:12:49.245
So you all wasted the only sunny Saturday
in the last two months to. what. care?

220
00:12:49.269 --> 00:12:50.913
You're right. super useful.

221
00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:53.040
Okay. I'm sorry. It's not like
it's our own personal money.

222
00:12:53.064 --> 00:12:54.834
The stolen funds
were meant for a stop sign

223
00:12:54.858 --> 00:12:56.778
in the intersection
where Robin had her accident.

224
00:13:00.489 --> 00:13:02.592
Count me in. Who do I bludgeon?

225
00:13:02.616 --> 00:13:06.369
Anderson. [sighs] We need
to break into his office to prove it.

226
00:13:19.674 --> 00:13:21.694
What the...?

227
00:13:21.718 --> 00:13:22.844
Great.

228
00:13:38.151 --> 00:13:39.754
Elle.

229
00:13:39.778 --> 00:13:42.298
Ms. Burke. Hi!

230
00:13:42.322 --> 00:13:43.466
Hi.

231
00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:47.512
Oh. I'm just coming from the bathroom.

232
00:13:47.536 --> 00:13:49.764
You know. taking the scenic route.

233
00:13:49.788 --> 00:13:51.974
Got to keep the blood flowing. right?

234
00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:55.061
Detention's the enemy
of cardiovascular health.

235
00:13:55.085 --> 00:13:56.604
Detention?

236
00:13:56.628 --> 00:13:59.089
Doesn't sound like Elle Woods.

237
00:14:00.382 --> 00:14:03.694
If anyone asks.
I threw a pie in Anderson's face.

238
00:14:03.718 --> 00:14:05.738
Wha... [clears throat] What?

239
00:14:05.762 --> 00:14:08.407
I didn't actually.
but all my friends got detention.

240
00:14:08.431 --> 00:14:12.370
so I decided to join them
for moral support.

241
00:14:12.394 --> 00:14:15.748
Oh. Protective and caring.

242
00:14:15.772 --> 00:14:17.583
How very Cancer of you.

243
00:14:17.607 --> 00:14:19.418
Oh. I'm a Gemini.

244
00:14:19.442 --> 00:14:21.921
Oh. Maybe cusp. then.

245
00:14:21.945 --> 00:14:24.006
No. My birthday is June 20th.

246
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:25.550
Purebred Gemini.

247
00:14:25.574 --> 00:14:27.492
My-my sister is Gemini rising.

248
00:14:28.493 --> 00:14:29.971
Or Gemini moon?

249
00:14:29.995 --> 00:14:31.722
Or she dated a Gemini?

250
00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:33.349
Wow. I have got to call my sister.

251
00:14:33.373 --> 00:14:35.726
Sorry. Uh. you should...

252
00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:37.687
-you should get back to detention.
-Yes.

253
00:14:37.711 --> 00:14:40.231
Oh. well. there is something
I never thought I'd say to you.

254
00:14:40.255 --> 00:14:42.483
-You and me both.
-Oh.

255
00:14:42.507 --> 00:14:43.776
Don't forget to sign up
for the Science Fair!

256
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:45.260
Got it.

257
00:14:46.052 --> 00:14:48.489
Welcome to Medina Town Hall.

258
00:14:48.513 --> 00:14:51.117
Like any other hall in any other town.

259
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:53.536
You brought me here to do... what?

260
00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:57.873
Well. when we first met.
you were very...

261
00:14:57.897 --> 00:15:00.042
honest about my campaign
needing a refresh.

262
00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:02.336
But I don't know anything
about political speeches.

263
00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:04.112
You know about presentation.

264
00:15:05.196 --> 00:15:07.550
All right? If it wasn't for you.
I would still have that mustache

265
00:15:07.574 --> 00:15:09.677
that nobody else told me
made me look like a serial killer.

266
00:15:09.701 --> 00:15:10.845
Ooh.

267
00:15:10.869 --> 00:15:13.764
And I would still be dressing like. um...

268
00:15:13.788 --> 00:15:14.849
Ted Bundy.

269
00:15:14.873 --> 00:15:17.810
I was gonna say
Jordan Catalano. but...

270
00:15:17.834 --> 00:15:21.731
From My So-Called Life? No.

271
00:15:21.755 --> 00:15:24.317
Here's my question.

272
00:15:24.341 --> 00:15:26.051
How do I get people to like me?

273
00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:32.908
You'll be presenting here?

274
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:35.393
-Mm-hmm.
-And against that color scheme?

275
00:15:36.353 --> 00:15:37.771
You're gonna be standing?

276
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:42.668
All right. get up there.
Let's see how the people will see you.

277
00:15:42.692 --> 00:15:44.319
Okay.

278
00:15:49.616 --> 00:15:51.969
Yikes.

279
00:15:51.993 --> 00:15:53.554
That's what I'm talking about.

280
00:15:53.578 --> 00:15:55.056
-Nixon.
-Oh.

281
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:56.599
He sweat through his first debate
with Kennedy.

282
00:15:56.623 --> 00:15:59.042
-It cost him the entire election.
-Okay.

283
00:16:00.126 --> 00:16:02.730
We're gonna need some powder foundation.

284
00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:04.565
some incandescent lighting.

285
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:09.528
and I will send you to my chiropractor
to work on your posture a bit.

286
00:16:09.552 --> 00:16:10.988
And I know you've been kind of

287
00:16:11.012 --> 00:16:15.576
experimenting with a few things up there.
but I'm just gonna fly out my hairstylist.

288
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:18.245
Great.

289
00:16:18.269 --> 00:16:21.749
Cool. You want to come check out
my campaign office after this?

290
00:16:21.773 --> 00:16:25.836
Oh. I would love to. but I got to
pick Elle up from detention at 3:00.

291
00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:27.380
Detention?

292
00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:29.632
She seemed so sweet
when she was cajoling me

293
00:16:29.656 --> 00:16:31.550
into renting a booth for her homecoming.

294
00:16:31.574 --> 00:16:34.679
Yeah. she has some ludicrous theory

295
00:16:34.703 --> 00:16:37.640
about her principal stealing funds
from the school.

296
00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:39.975
Can you go to the other podium?

297
00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:43.396
Your better angle
needs to face the TV cameras.

298
00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:44.605
Hold on.

299
00:16:44.629 --> 00:16:47.358
E-Elle thinks that Shane Anderson
is stealing money?

300
00:16:47.382 --> 00:16:52.137
Yes. And she can be very convincing
when she's invested in something.

301
00:16:54.723 --> 00:16:58.309
I think our best bet is
to do this by candlelight.

302
00:17:07.152 --> 00:17:08.504
Phase One is complete.

303
00:17:08.528 --> 00:17:10.196
Is Phase Two killing Anderson?

304
00:17:11.406 --> 00:17:13.175
-You guys told Kimberly?
-I was forced.

305
00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:14.844
Oh. like someone forced you

306
00:17:14.868 --> 00:17:16.679
-to wear those pants?
-Remember when you got nicer?

307
00:17:16.703 --> 00:17:17.847
Can we go back to that?

308
00:17:17.871 --> 00:17:19.682
Okay. Phase Two.

309
00:17:19.706 --> 00:17:23.668
What does "Consolidate and secure
personal care essentials" mean?

310
00:17:40.351 --> 00:17:41.412
Can I help you?

311
00:17:41.436 --> 00:17:44.439
That looks so familiar.

312
00:17:45.148 --> 00:17:48.461
Oh. yeah. it's Cujo.
I kind of thought was banned.

313
00:17:48.485 --> 00:17:51.630
and I will therefore be

314
00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:55.509
prominently placing it right...

315
00:17:55.533 --> 00:17:56.969
here.

316
00:17:56.993 --> 00:17:59.180
No. Your bracelet.

317
00:17:59.204 --> 00:18:01.307
Camp Saddle Rock.

318
00:18:01.331 --> 00:18:05.394
I saw it earlier and thought.
"Who have I seen wearing that before?"

319
00:18:05.418 --> 00:18:10.024
And then I thought.
"Wait. Liz has that bracelet."

320
00:18:10.048 --> 00:18:12.175
-And then I thought...
-Get there faster.

321
00:18:13.468 --> 00:18:15.696
Were you two at camp at the same time?

322
00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:17.865
Why in the world would that matter?

323
00:18:17.889 --> 00:18:21.243
I'm just trying to figure out
what your damage is with each other.

324
00:18:21.267 --> 00:18:22.769
With you and me...

325
00:18:24.562 --> 00:18:26.582
-We don't need to recap.
-Mm.

326
00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.793
But Liz is. like.
the most neutral force ever.

327
00:18:28.817 --> 00:18:30.878
I'm sorry.
but Liz is not neutral.

328
00:18:30.902 --> 00:18:33.339
Okay. so something did happen.

329
00:18:33.363 --> 00:18:34.632
Did you have a big fight?

330
00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:36.342
You know. this might shock you.

331
00:18:36.366 --> 00:18:39.619
but our lives didn't just start
the second you appeared at this school.

332
00:18:48.920 --> 00:18:51.398
What the hell is
a friendship sabbatical?

333
00:18:51.422 --> 00:18:52.858
What?

334
00:18:52.882 --> 00:18:55.069
You and the running man are being weird.

335
00:18:55.093 --> 00:18:57.988
What? No. we're not.

336
00:18:58.012 --> 00:18:59.198
Stop playing with fire!

337
00:18:59.222 --> 00:19:00.908
I'm not! Everyone's fine!

338
00:19:00.932 --> 00:19:02.600
You'll burn the place down.

339
00:19:05.687 --> 00:19:08.833
Why are the quiet ones always pyromaniacs?

340
00:19:08.857 --> 00:19:11.025
And isn't Cujo banned?

341
00:19:13.403 --> 00:19:14.696
I'm moving to self-help.

342
00:19:30.837 --> 00:19:34.883
So. uh. I hear you and I are
on some sort of embargo.

343
00:19:36.092 --> 00:19:38.070
Embargo. sabbatical.

344
00:19:38.094 --> 00:19:40.680
Where are we. a thesaurus convention?

345
00:19:44.976 --> 00:19:46.370
Are you okay?

346
00:19:46.394 --> 00:19:47.746
Yep.

347
00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:50.398
You just shelved R. L. Stine in self-help.

348
00:19:51.691 --> 00:19:55.504
One could argue
his entire repertoire is a metaphor

349
00:19:55.528 --> 00:19:58.382
for the horrors of teen adolescence.

350
00:19:58.406 --> 00:19:59.616
One could.

351
00:20:02.785 --> 00:20:04.245
I messed up.

352
00:20:05.663 --> 00:20:07.832
Maybe I shouldn't have told Shannon.

353
00:20:08.833 --> 00:20:11.061
You were tiki drunk at her mom's memorial.

354
00:20:11.085 --> 00:20:13.212
I know. I-I screwed up.

355
00:20:14.505 --> 00:20:16.567
But we both tried calling her.

356
00:20:16.591 --> 00:20:18.092
She doesn't want to talk to us.

357
00:20:19.093 --> 00:20:20.613
I'm not sure what else we can do.

358
00:20:20.637 --> 00:20:22.573
Nothing. We do nothing.

359
00:20:22.597 --> 00:20:24.909
No more extended eye contact.

360
00:20:24.933 --> 00:20:27.119
no more leaning against lockers.

361
00:20:27.143 --> 00:20:28.746
-no more...
-No speaking to each other?

362
00:20:28.770 --> 00:20:31.898
I think we should avoid
anything involving mouths.

363
00:20:34.734 --> 00:20:36.420
Okay.

364
00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:40.406
Can I ask. respectfully. why?

365
00:20:41.866 --> 00:20:43.719
I mean. she already knows.

366
00:20:43.743 --> 00:20:45.244
She's not here.

367
00:20:48.247 --> 00:20:50.333
Because it's just not me. Miles.

368
00:20:51.334 --> 00:20:53.002
I'm not that kind of girl.

369
00:21:00.677 --> 00:21:03.948
Uh. there's a plumbing emergency
in the ladies' room.

370
00:21:03.972 --> 00:21:06.408
What? Did you say something?

371
00:21:06.432 --> 00:21:08.869
Toilet...

372
00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:10.496
exploded.

373
00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:13.147
I'll call Frank.

374
00:21:18.486 --> 00:21:19.737
That's my cue.

375
00:21:20.738 --> 00:21:22.156
Good luck.

376
00:21:31.249 --> 00:21:33.042
Aw. come on.

377
00:21:47.515 --> 00:21:49.600
Come on. come on. come on.

378
00:21:50.601 --> 00:21:52.454
Why does every key look the same?

379
00:21:52.478 --> 00:21:53.896
Miles?

380
00:21:56.274 --> 00:21:57.442
Principal Anderson.

381
00:22:04.032 --> 00:22:05.676
Hey.

382
00:22:05.700 --> 00:22:07.344
Did you drop this?

383
00:22:07.368 --> 00:22:09.179
-Hilarious.
-I thought so.

384
00:22:09.203 --> 00:22:10.764
Yeah. do you come up with these
ahead of time.

385
00:22:10.788 --> 00:22:12.808
or is this just. like.
off the top of your head?

386
00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:14.977
-Oh. you think I'm funny?
-Here's an idea.

387
00:22:15.001 --> 00:22:17.628
Why don't you two stop fighting about...

388
00:22:18.463 --> 00:22:20.441
the mineral economy.

389
00:22:20.465 --> 00:22:22.026
and start getting ready
for our next phase.

390
00:22:22.050 --> 00:22:23.134
Hey. guys.

391
00:22:24.302 --> 00:22:25.404
We're screwed.

392
00:22:25.428 --> 00:22:28.014
Sixty-one tampons!

393
00:22:28.598 --> 00:22:30.576
And that's not to mention the super pluses

394
00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:35.271
that got so engorged they became
one monster. uh. tampon rat king.

395
00:22:37.273 --> 00:22:39.877
-Yep. we're screwed.
-Fire. blood or flood.

396
00:22:39.901 --> 00:22:43.839
I am not to be bothered on my days off
unless there is a fire. blood or flood.

397
00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:46.365
and you all chose the latter.

398
00:22:47.075 --> 00:22:50.119
Mrs. Martindale.
you may take the rest of the day off.

399
00:22:53.498 --> 00:22:54.725
Uh...

400
00:22:54.749 --> 00:22:56.268
-They're all accounted for.
-Mm.

401
00:22:56.292 --> 00:22:57.770
The one in the hoodie's alive.

402
00:22:57.794 --> 00:22:59.670
He just looks comatose.

403
00:23:06.344 --> 00:23:07.571
Uh. Miss Woods?

404
00:23:07.595 --> 00:23:10.098
Yeah. might I ask what you're doing here?

405
00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:21.043
I am here to serve my time
just like everyone else.

406
00:23:21.067 --> 00:23:23.420
Uh-huh. Well. I'm just looking
at my roster here.

407
00:23:23.444 --> 00:23:26.423
I got the athlete. the basket case.
the princess.

408
00:23:26.447 --> 00:23:28.801
the criminal. but no Elle Woods. so...

409
00:23:28.825 --> 00:23:30.743
what are you doing here. Miss Woods?

410
00:23:32.954 --> 00:23:35.140
You remember.

411
00:23:35.164 --> 00:23:37.208
When I pied you in the face.

412
00:23:39.210 --> 00:23:41.438
When you... I'm sorry. when you what?

413
00:23:41.462 --> 00:23:43.357
You know.

414
00:23:43.381 --> 00:23:45.109
When I pied you in the face.

415
00:23:45.133 --> 00:23:48.195
I... no. I don't understand
anything you're saying.

416
00:23:48.219 --> 00:23:50.656
When she pied you in the face.

417
00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:52.390
Oh.

418
00:23:53.975 --> 00:23:58.497
You mean the lemon meringue you gifted me
for some woman thing?

419
00:23:58.521 --> 00:24:00.022
-Wha...
-What?

420
00:24:02.275 --> 00:24:04.193
Seriously! Why are you here?

421
00:24:09.532 --> 00:24:11.093
To scare myself straight.

422
00:24:11.117 --> 00:24:15.097
Well. I guess now you're here
because you lied.

423
00:24:15.121 --> 00:24:16.640
New deal.

424
00:24:16.664 --> 00:24:19.309
No more hall passes.

425
00:24:19.333 --> 00:24:24.064
We are all staying put until 3:00.

426
00:24:24.088 --> 00:24:26.150
What if we need
to use the facilities?

427
00:24:26.174 --> 00:24:28.485
Then I guess you're gonna
have to get familiar

428
00:24:28.509 --> 00:24:31.179
with the concept of holding it.

429
00:24:36.684 --> 00:24:39.896
Oh. my God. You're Ally Sheedy.

430
00:24:41.272 --> 00:24:43.083
-Elle Woods.
-No. in The Breakfast Club.

431
00:24:43.107 --> 00:24:44.960
there's the whole thing
where they learn that Ally Sheedy

432
00:24:44.984 --> 00:24:48.237
didn't even have to be in detention.
she just showed up.

433
00:24:50.907 --> 00:24:52.509
Okay. I couldn't do it.

434
00:24:52.533 --> 00:24:53.927
-I really tried.
-Mm-hmm.

435
00:24:53.951 --> 00:24:56.305
I even went to his office with the pie.

436
00:24:56.329 --> 00:24:58.932
But I'm not a natural rule breaker.

437
00:24:58.956 --> 00:25:01.602
and the consequences
really flash before your eyes

438
00:25:01.626 --> 00:25:03.211
once you're face-to-face with them.

439
00:25:04.170 --> 00:25:06.190
Can you imagine
what it's like inside her head?

440
00:25:06.214 --> 00:25:07.691
Wait. I'm sorry.
I thought that I was Ally Sheedy.

441
00:25:07.715 --> 00:25:10.301
and I thought
that you were Molly Ringwald.

442
00:25:11.302 --> 00:25:12.404
Am I Molly Ringwald?

443
00:25:12.428 --> 00:25:13.780
Maybe we should have

444
00:25:13.804 --> 00:25:15.699
seen it coming
that Elle's bad at being bad.

445
00:25:15.723 --> 00:25:17.284
Guys. whatever.

446
00:25:17.308 --> 00:25:18.994
Elle's a model citizen. We knew this.

447
00:25:19.018 --> 00:25:20.704
We have more important things
to deal with right now.

448
00:25:20.728 --> 00:25:22.271
We need a plan B.

449
00:25:45.211 --> 00:25:47.689
-Yo. Kyle.
-Mm-hmm? Mm-hmm?

450
00:25:47.713 --> 00:25:49.608
Wake up.

451
00:25:49.632 --> 00:25:51.777
You wouldn't happen to have your. uh...

452
00:25:51.801 --> 00:25:54.029
you-know-what. would you?

453
00:25:54.053 --> 00:25:55.805
Have his what?

454
00:26:03.521 --> 00:26:05.940
All right. Mr. Chuckles.
I'll see you soon.

455
00:26:09.443 --> 00:26:10.587
Principal Anderson.

456
00:26:10.611 --> 00:26:13.215
we need you to settle an argument for us.

457
00:26:13.239 --> 00:26:16.117
Do I actually need a pregnancy test
to know that I'm pregnant?

458
00:26:17.368 --> 00:26:19.554
-Uh...
-I vote yes.

459
00:26:19.578 --> 00:26:21.890
And I feel like those tests
are just the patriarchy

460
00:26:21.914 --> 00:26:23.850
trying to normalize corporations
charging women money for something

461
00:26:23.874 --> 00:26:25.269
they already know about their own bodies.

462
00:26:25.293 --> 00:26:26.687
Hmm. good point.

463
00:26:26.711 --> 00:26:27.896
I do know when I'm ovulating.

464
00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:28.814
-Mm-hmm.
-Boo.

465
00:26:28.838 --> 00:26:29.982
Thoughts?

466
00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:31.149
Um...

467
00:26:31.173 --> 00:26:33.694
Well. have you talked
to your parents about this?

468
00:26:33.718 --> 00:26:36.238
Oh. my parents are religious.

469
00:26:36.262 --> 00:26:37.763
We can't talk about sex.

470
00:26:39.724 --> 00:26:42.327
Yeah. um. see Mrs. Nelson

471
00:26:42.351 --> 00:26:44.246
in the guidance counselor's office
next week.

472
00:26:44.270 --> 00:26:45.998
I'm sure she has a pamphlet.

473
00:26:46.022 --> 00:26:47.732
Yeah. or something like that.

474
00:26:50.026 --> 00:26:51.027
Okay.

475
00:26:52.695 --> 00:26:54.381
-Hmm.
-I felt a kick.

476
00:26:54.405 --> 00:26:56.633
Oh. Oh.

477
00:26:56.657 --> 00:26:57.926
Is that a contraction?

478
00:26:57.950 --> 00:26:59.845
Yeah. I think that's what those feel like.

479
00:26:59.869 --> 00:27:01.346
Like. it itches. right?

480
00:27:01.370 --> 00:27:02.788
Uh...

481
00:27:04.665 --> 00:27:06.101
Does anyone hear that?

482
00:27:06.125 --> 00:27:07.352
Hear what?

483
00:27:07.376 --> 00:27:09.271
I think it's coming
from the ceiling.

484
00:27:09.295 --> 00:27:10.921
Oh. my God. is that a rat?

485
00:27:12.381 --> 00:27:13.984
What? A rat?

486
00:27:14.008 --> 00:27:15.819
Yeah. you don't hear
those little toenails?

487
00:27:15.843 --> 00:27:17.696
We should call maintenance.

488
00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:19.972
No. no. no. no. no. No. no. no.

489
00:27:21.057 --> 00:27:23.118
This can wait until Monday.

490
00:27:23.142 --> 00:27:24.352
Oh.

491
00:27:31.442 --> 00:27:32.735
Oh.

492
00:27:34.528 --> 00:27:35.839
-Yikes.
-Principal Anderson.

493
00:27:35.863 --> 00:27:38.925
if there is a rat trapped
in our school air ducts.

494
00:27:38.949 --> 00:27:42.763
we... as the most evolved species
of mammal in this room...

495
00:27:42.787 --> 00:27:44.598
are responsible for its well-being.

496
00:27:44.622 --> 00:27:46.058
-Mm-hmm.
-It's a rat.

497
00:27:46.082 --> 00:27:49.144
A rat without access to food or water.

498
00:27:49.168 --> 00:27:50.729
not to mention daylight.

499
00:27:50.753 --> 00:27:53.357
When was the last time
these vents were cleaned?

500
00:27:53.381 --> 00:27:54.483
Anyone?

501
00:27:54.507 --> 00:27:56.943
I genuinely have no idea.

502
00:27:56.967 --> 00:27:59.780
Do I need to make a call
in to PETA's own Linda McCartney

503
00:27:59.804 --> 00:28:04.493
and alert her to the inhumane
living conditions at Rainier West High?

504
00:28:04.517 --> 00:28:06.727
Also. if it dies. it'll smell really bad.

505
00:28:19.865 --> 00:28:21.760
Hey. Frank. it's Shane.

506
00:28:21.784 --> 00:28:22.928
Yeah.

507
00:28:22.952 --> 00:28:27.182
Uh. eh... would you mind bringing
a ladder up to the library?

508
00:28:27.206 --> 00:28:29.208
Oh. and a jar of peanut butter.

509
00:28:31.419 --> 00:28:33.421
For the rat. not for me.

510
00:28:38.968 --> 00:28:40.362
